Lazio’s Italian forward Ciro Immobile celebrates after scoring an equalizer during the Italian Serie A football match AS Rome vs Lazio Rome on September 29, 2018, at the Olympic stadium in Rome. / AFP PHOTO / Alberto PIZZOLI Lazio stars Ciro Immobile and Sergej Milinkovic-Savic have extended both their contracts with the Serie A club until 2023, the Roman outfit confirmed on Monday. Italian international Immobile — the top scorer in Serie A last season with 29 goals — and Serb Milinkovic-Savic will earn over three millions euros ($3.5 million) a year plus bonuses — a record for the Italian club. Lazio are seventh in Serie A after seven matches, having lost the capital derby 3-1 to city rivals Roma on Saturday. Simone Inzaghi’s side travel to Eintracht Frankfurt in the Europa League on Thursday. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .